headline: Kenvue beats quarterly estimates, announces job cuts amid Kimberly-Clark acquisition
summary: Feb 17 () - Tylenol-maker Kenvue on Tuesday beat Wall Street estimates for fourth-quarter results and announced a global workforce reduction, as ‌it proceeds toward a planned takeover by Kimberly-Clark. Kenvue said its board ‌has approved a plan to optimize its operating model, resulting in a net reduction of its ​global workforce by about 3.
